org.knime.core.node.dialog

Interface InputNode


  • public interface InputNode
    Interface for nodes that can be controlled by input from external sources, e.g. web services.
    Since:
    2.12
    Author:
    Thorsten Meinl, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ExternalNodeData getInputData()
      Returns a template for the expected input data.
      void setInputData(ExternalNodeData inputData)
      Sets the input for the node.
      void validateInputData(ExternalNodeData inputData)
      Validates the input for the node.

    • Method Detail

      • getInputData

        ExternalNodeData getInputData()
        Returns a template for the expected input data. Clients may use the templates, replace values, and set the via setInputData(ExternalNodeData). If the node reads larger amount from an external resource you must specifiy a URL in the data object (e.g. the default location from the dialog).
        Returns:
        a template for the input data

      • validateInputData

        void validateInputData(ExternalNodeData inputData)
                throws InvalidSettingsException
        Validates the input for the node. Implementation should only check if the data is applicable but not load it into the node. If the data is not applicable, an InvalidSettingsException must be thrown and callers should avoid calling setInputData(ExternalNodeData).
        Parameters:
        inputData - an external node data object
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - if the data is invalid

      • setInputData

        void setInputData(ExternalNodeData inputData)
           throws InvalidSettingsException
        Sets the input for the node. Implementations must make sure that the nodes internal configuration is updated accordingly so that the next execution uses the provided input data. If the data is not applicable (which should not happen if validateInputData(ExternalNodeData) has been called before) then an InvalidSettingsException should be thrown.
        Parameters:
        inputData - an external node data object
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - if the data is invalid
